<p align="justify">
My research fields are mathematics, computer science, and applied physics. My interests include: discrete geometry, polyhedral combinatorics, geometric topology, computer simulation and the physics of granular media. See my <a href="index.php?l=3">research page</a> and my <a href="index.php?l=4">list of publications</a> for more details.
</p>

<p align="justify">
I got my habilitation at the <a href="http://www.univ-paris-diderot.fr/">University of Paris 7</a>.
Before moving back to France, I was 
<!--a professor at the <a href="http://www.ehl.edu">&Eacute;cole Hoteli&egrave;re de Lausanne</a>, and-->
a lecturer in Operations Research at the <a href="http://www.epfl.ch">&Eacute;cole Polytechnique F&eacute;d&eacute;rale de Lausanne</a>, in Switzerland where I did my PhD under the supervision of <a href="http://people.epfl.ch/thomas.liebling">Tom Liebling</a>.
</p>
